data.title: Num!!!
data.text: I always have this one dish that has lobster, scallops, shrimp and other good vegetables. My daughter and I split it and we still have as much to bring home to our houses. For about $25 that is a great meal!

data.title: Great lunch deals!
data.text:
Fast service, good food!
If you need a quick sushi fix, this is the place to go.  The lunch menu is super cheap and super good.

data.title: Back for seconds
data.text: A year after the first time and its still a great place for dinner. They added a ceviche since and it is wonderful!  My overly picky son loved the thai calamari.

data.title: Great Sushi Place
data.text:
Love this place for sushi! 

I'm not sure why more people don't go to this restaurant. Whenever we go it's usually pretty empty. 

But they have very good sushi!

data.title: EXTREMELY DISSATISFIED
data.text:
My family and I decided to stop by this restaurant to celebrate Father's Day on a Wednesday night at around 8 pm.  The 7 of us walked in and wanted to sit out on the patio. As we walked out there and saw that there were not many people and a large table of 10+ people finished with being served and preparing to leave, the server came out and told us we could not sit outside as only one table is set up for parties more than 7. We asked if we could combine two high tables - to which the waitress said she'd ask her manager. I was sure that the MANAGER would say, sure, we will accommodate as we are not that busy.  I was very wrong - the waitress came out and told us we could not sit outside due to reservations - really? People had sushi reservations at 8:15 pm on a Wednesday night? I don't buy it for a second. 

When we decided to eat inside where all the tables literally sit on top of each other, it was over 10 minutes before the waitress acknowledged us.

I called the next day (today) to speak to the manager about this disgusting experience only to be told she was not in yet and to try back later. I asked if there was only one manager and of course, the answer was yes. So, because it's probably the same manager that told us NO, I figured I'd share my review to a larger audience.

FYI: I am a 30 year native of the community where this restaurant is located and can say with certainty that they don't stand a chance. The location they occupy has had about 8 restaurants occupy the space in the last 5 years. BUST.

data.title: Yuck
data.text: The sushi was like buying it at the grocery store. The crab was imitation crab sticks, the rice was mushy. Just really cheap bad sushi. Outdoor area was nice to sit at. Friday evening and the place was dead.

data.title: Part 5 of Fl to Alaska.
data.text: We sat at the Sushi bar and were not diapointed. I have been strict Vegan since 1/1/16 but tonight I had some of the best prepared and tasty sushi I could have asked for. Great Miso soup,seaweed salad and Sopporo beer on tap. My brother had hibachi and said it was also great, Our wives  had the masterpiece you see in the attached photo and we ended up doggy baging some home. Would highly recommend.

data.title: Definitely our favorite Hibachi restaurant.
data.text: Kintaro is close to home for us, 10 minutes and about 5 minutes from my wife's employment. We overlooked them the first year or so they were in business but now wonder why we didn't try them sooner. The Hibachi  side features a a grill for up to 8 or 10 people with an entertaing show by the chef. We love the Filet with Scallops. We order the Fried Rice with every meal. The servings are generous including the entree choice. It is a fun atmosphere with terrific food. Looking forward to going back soon.

data.title: Good sushi and fast service
data.text: We stopped in here for lunch on a Friday and it was fairly busy.  In fact, there were quite a few Firemen eating there.  The menu is large and the assortment of Maki rolls gives you many options.  Our waitress was very prompt as was the making of our rolls and bento box.  The fish was a bit warm for my taste but it was fresh and the prices were about average.  Recommended!

data.title: Excellent happy hour specials.
data.text: We go here a lot for the Happy hour specials ,$2 ciders and Fried Dumplings , Orange Chicken is very good.  We always like our food and it has a nice atmosphere.

data.title: Hibachi with Honda Show
data.text:
Ask for Honda when you make your reservation. He is passionate about quality, tells great stories, and most importantly is a great Hibachi Chef. Scallops, shrimp, steak, chicken or salmon are all good choices. 
Sunday is an all day happy hour with drink specials.
Don't forget the sushi.  They have bar seating on front of the chefs. That is a fun show for a single or may even a group of 2 or 3.  Other seating is available too.
This is a big deal to me, the entire staff is very hardworking and genuinely nice.

data.title: Good variety
data.text: We went here with friends. They have a large menu and you can pick habachi or the regular menu. Lots of sushi and Asian inspired dishes. Prices are very reasonable. Good drink menu.  Our server was Stephanie  and she was wonderful  making suggestions  and explaining  any questions  we had. They also have a VIP club that give you discounts and Birthday  coupons. We would definitely go back.

data.title: Best Sushi I've Had!
data.text:
Stopped by for lunch on my way to the airport. Didn't know what to expect.
Long story short, sat at the sushi bar. Saw the chef present a plate of sushi to a customer sitting near me. I asked the chef what it was. He said, "The special."
I ordered The Special. It was by far the best sushi I have ever had!
Now I need to go back to try the Japanese grill.

data.title: Great Sushi
data.text: Was there with my wife. Food was fantastic. Ceviche was delicious, loved the sushi and they have my favorite quail eggs. Definitely recommend.

data.title: Nice surprise!
data.text:
Great food!!!  We tried the sweet potato tempera as and appetizer and it was great!  Then on to the sushi.  We had the California roll, the ISO roll and the Pink Lady.  All three looked too good to eat.  Reasonably priced and our waitress was fantastic.

Was meeting a friend for sushi, but didn't know where to go.  Asked Siri and she suggested several restaurants in the area.  We just randomly choose because we had never been there.  Do not overlook this place if you are looking for sushi.  Some of the best sushi we have eaten!

data.title: Beautiful place with FABULOUS sushi!
data.text: We love this little gem.  We are always seated quickly, and love to sit right at the small sushi bar and watch the artists at work.  The hibachi tables are also lovely and the food is great.  The prices during their lunch and happy hour are super reasonable too!

data.title: good japanese food
data.text: food quality was average, amount average, price average.  Nothing particularly unique but, overall good.

data.title: Hibachi Lunch
data.text: My husband and I had lunch at this place for the first time. The hibachi chef is a lot of fun to watch. The seasonings for each item from the miso soup to the shrimp are spot on. The prices are excellent and good lunch-size portions. They have a huge selection of sushi to choose from but we didn't try any of those. I will be sampling those on our next visit.

data.title: Enjoyed the Hibachi on one visit, was disappointed with the sushi on the next visit
data.text:
Two visits, two experiences.

Soccer team hibachi night was a blast.  The boys loved the show and the food.  I was underwhelmed with the beef, but the shrimp and chicken were good as was the fried rice.

Next day after a game, we went in to try the sushi.  The small sashimi slices and bland specialty rolls made for a disappointing second visit here.  The manager was very gracious and recognized me from the previous night, but the sushi was subpar.  Too much rice and too little fish that was not top quality.

Go for the hibachi with a large group.  Avoid the raw stuff.
